{{Other uses|Inflow (disambiguation){{!}}Inflow}}
{{unreferenced|date=May 2017}}
[[File:Pescone alla foce.jpg|thumb|Torrente Pescone, one of the inflows of [[Lake Orta]] ([[Italy]]).]]
In [[hydrology]], the '''inflow''' of a [[body of water]] is the source of the [[water]] in the body of water. It can also refer to the average [[volume]] of incoming water in unit [[time]]. It is contrasted with [[outflow (hydrology)|outflow]].

==Overview==
All bodies of water have multiple inflows, but often, one inflow may predominate and be the largest source of water. However, in many cases, no single inflow will predominate and there will be multiple primary inflows. For a [[lake]], the inflow may be a [[river]] or [[stream]] that literally flows into the lake. Inflow may also be, strictly speaking, not flows, but rather [[precipitation (meteorology)|precipitation]], like [[rain]]. 

Inflow can also be used to refer to [[groundwater recharge]].

