[[File:Diplomatic missions of Saint Kitts and Nevis.png|thumb|right|400px|Diplomatic missions of Saint Kitts and Nevis]]
[[File:High Commission of Saint Kitts and Nevis, London & High Commission of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, London.jpg|thumb|right|High Commission of Saint Kitts and Nevis in London]]
[[Image:Embassy Antigua et al.jpg|right|thumb|Embassy of Saint Kitts and Nevis in Washington, DC]]
This is a '''list of diplomatic missions of Saint Kitts and Nevis''', which operate under the authority of the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Saint Kitts and Nevis)|Kittitian Ministry of Foreign Affairs]]. The [[Caribbean]] island of [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]] has a modest diplomatic presence.  Its mission to the [[European Union]] in [[Brussels]] is shared with other East [[Caribbean]] states. It recognizes the [[Republic of China]] and consequently has an embassy in [[Taipei]].

==Americas==
*{{CAN}}
** [[Ottawa]] (High Commission)
*{{CUB}}
** [[Havana]] (Embassy)
*{{JAM}}
** [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]] (High Commission)
*{{USA}}
** [[Washington, D.C.]] (Embassy)
**[[Los Angeles]] (Consulate-General)
**[[New York City|New York]] (Consulate-General)

==Asia==
*{{ROC-TWN}}
** [[Taipei]] (Embassy)
*{{ARE}}
** [[Dubai]] (Consulate-General)

==Europe==
*{{BEL}}
** [[Brussels]] (Embassy)
*{{GBR}}
** [[London]] ([[High Commission of Saint Kitts and Nevis, London|High Commission]])

==Multilateral organisations==
* {{EU}}
**[[Brussels]] (Mission)
* {{UNO}}
**[[New York City|New York]] (Permanent Mission)

