'''The Dance of the Peacock: An Anthology of English Poetry from India''' is a collection of poems written by one hundred and fifty one poets; edited by Dr Vivekanand Jha. The one hundred and fifty one poets include Indians and diasporic Indians.The book was published by Hidden Brook Press, Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hiddenbrookpress.com/Book-Indo-EnglishPoetry.html|title=The Dance of the Peacock||work=www.HiddenBrookPress.com|archive-url=|access-date=28 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=5M5ongEACAAJ&dq=The+Dance+of+the+Peacock:+An+Anthology+of+English+Poetry+from+India+awards&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjvgaes3IPdAhXMPo8KHf4yCT8Q6AEIJjAA|title=The Dance of the Peacock|publisher=Hidden Brook Press, Canada|year=2013|isbn=1927725003|location=Canada|pages=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Dance of the Peacock |url=http://www.boloji.com/articles/14771/the-dance-of-the-peacock |website=boloji.com |publisher=boloji.com |accessdate=30 August 2018}}</ref>
== Synopsis == The authors has different outlooks towards life in their poems mostly because of the variation in their living environment and their age differences. The name of the book simply compares the poetry to the dance of the peacock. Most of the authors are Indian diaspora in UK, US and Canada. The writers are a mix of male and female.<ref>{{cite web |title=The dance of the peacock : an anthology of English poetry from India |url=https://searchworks.stanford.edu/view/10411735 |website=searchworks.stanford.edu |publisher=searchworks.stanford.edu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Poetry: Anthologies |url=http://www.shantaacharya.com/assets/html/shantaAcharya_poetry_anthologies.html |website=shantaacharya.com |publisher=shantaacharya.com |accessdate=30 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/books/books-authors/a-poem-a-day/article5052407.ece|title=A poem a day|date=|work=The Hindu|access-date=28 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=MA Creative Writing student in The Dance of the Peacock |url=https://www.londonmet.ac.uk/news/articles/ma-creative-writing-student-mona-dashs-poetry-is-published-in-the-dance-of-the-peacock-/ |website=londonmet.ac.uk |publisher=londonmet.ac.uk |accessdate=30 August 2018}}</ref>
